WEBVTT

00:42.126 --> 00:43.334
(TWITTERING)

00:49.800 --> 00:51.217
MAN: Better here?

00:52.428 --> 00:53.469
Or better here?

00:55.931 --> 00:58.891
Better here?
Or better here?

00:58.976 --> 01:00.309
You don't want to be
walking around blind

01:00.477 --> 01:02.145
at Christmas, Mrs. Ryor.
Help me out.

01:02.646 --> 01:04.397
I don't
need glasses.

01:04.480 --> 01:07.525
You need binoculars.
We're settling for glasses.

01:08.152 --> 01:09.444
Better one...

01:09.528 --> 01:11.487
Glasses will
make me look old.

01:20.831 --> 01:22.165
Try these.

01:30.549 --> 01:32.508
I look hot.

01:37.264 --> 01:38.431
Evening,
Father Bruce.

01:38.515 --> 01:39.891
Hello,
Dr. Finch.

01:41.226 --> 01:43.019
Hello, Mrs. Patterson.
Hello, Dr. Finch.

01:51.445 --> 01:52.820
Dr. Finch!

01:52.946 --> 01:54.280
Hello, Gustave, Gerta.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.573
I'd love to chat
and so,

01:55.699 --> 01:57.575
but you know how focused
Gerta gets on our runs.

01:58.368 --> 01:59.660
Oh, Gerta!

01:59.745 --> 02:00.745
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

02:02.206 --> 02:03.372
Auf Wiedersehen.

02:03.457 --> 02:06.959
Auf Wiedersehen.
You should maybe
get that looked at.

02:07.044 --> 02:08.252
And start wearing
some padding.

02:08.336 --> 02:09.419
GUSTAVE: Gut, gut, gut.

02:09.505 --> 02:11.964
Yes, well, I'm sure it's
more fun your way, Arturo,

02:12.049 --> 02:14.133
but I need you to
hang the decorations,

02:14.218 --> 02:15.968
not just chuck 'em up there
and hope they stick.

02:16.053 --> 02:17.094
Hey. Steve.

02:17.221 --> 02:18.304
Mayor Young.

02:18.388 --> 02:20.306
What do you think?
Lookin' good.

02:20.390 --> 02:21.557
Thank you.

02:21.725 --> 02:22.850
Is that...
Is that an angel on top?

02:22.935 --> 02:25.645
(CHUCKLES) It's supposed
to be, but we couldn't
find one big enough.

02:25.729 --> 02:27.939
Fortunately my wife has
a porcelain doll collection,

02:28.023 --> 02:29.565
so she lent us
her Marilyn Monroe.

02:29.817 --> 02:32.151
Nice touch.
Looks good.

02:32.236 --> 02:34.987
Yeah. Don't go overboard
with the lights though.
We don't want to seem tacky.

02:35.072 --> 02:37.698
Whatever you say, Steve.
Winterfest is your baby.
Hey, hey.

02:37.783 --> 02:39.659
We got any big surprises
this year?

02:39.743 --> 02:43.454
Come on. Come on. Nobody
keeps a secret better
than me. For instance...

02:44.331 --> 02:46.165
(CLEARS THROAT)
I know for a fact,

02:46.250 --> 02:48.751
Sheriff Dave
is a cross-dresser.

02:49.253 --> 02:51.170
I never told a soul.

02:51.255 --> 02:53.297
Until today.

03:37.342 --> 03:39.135
Hi, honey. I'm home.

03:42.014 --> 03:43.764
It's the raw
quail eggs, isn't it?

03:43.849 --> 03:46.976
It's the texture, right?
The grainy, slimy, milky...

03:47.311 --> 03:48.603
Can you taste the curry?

03:48.729 --> 03:50.021
Yeah. Yeah.

03:51.106 --> 03:53.274
Gee, I sure hope
there's more of that.

03:53.358 --> 03:55.484
You are such a bad liar.

03:56.153 --> 03:58.154
I knew it was awful.
It's awful, right?

03:58.739 --> 03:59.822
Yeah.

04:00.449 --> 04:01.490
Who wants pizza?

04:04.161 --> 04:06.954
My life just isn't
working out the way
I thought it would.

04:07.039 --> 04:08.080
Excuse me?

04:08.165 --> 04:10.249
Oh, honey,
you don't mean that.

04:10.334 --> 04:12.543
I'm 10, and
what have I really
accomplished?

04:13.086 --> 04:14.629
A half season
of soccer.

04:15.047 --> 04:17.173
Cleared legendary
mode of Halo.

04:17.632 --> 04:20.259
A lackluster stint
in the Cub Scouts.

04:20.761 --> 04:23.179
Hey. Hey.
Guess what day it is.

04:23.680 --> 04:24.680
Come on. Guess.

04:25.223 --> 04:26.390
Maddy.

04:26.475 --> 04:28.559
I don't know,
and I don't care.

04:29.019 --> 04:30.186
Wrong.

04:31.188 --> 04:32.772
It's December 1.

04:33.857 --> 04:35.066
(GROANS)

04:35.776 --> 04:36.984
KELLY: Oh!

04:37.069 --> 04:39.153
Time to break out
the Christmas calendar.

04:39.988 --> 04:41.864
Yes.
This is a busy time of year,

04:42.032 --> 04:43.908
so we have to
have a game plan.

04:44.701 --> 04:47.828
Okay. December 3,
we hang the wreath.

04:50.624 --> 04:52.500
You just get so intense
about Christmas.

04:52.584 --> 04:55.294
I'm not intense.
I'm just extremely organized.

04:55.379 --> 04:56.796
When you're talking about
Christmas caroling,

04:56.880 --> 04:59.382
you shouldn't have
to use the term
"flanking maneuver."

04:59.508 --> 05:02.635
Look. Look,
I know it's only December 1...
Uh-huh.

05:02.719 --> 05:05.179
...but I have all
the planning to do
for the Winterfest.

05:05.263 --> 05:08.057
You have a cookbook to write.
The kids have school.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.434
It all goes by
so quickly.

05:10.519 --> 05:12.061
Before you know it,
Christmas will be over.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.647
Yeah, but that doesn't
mean that we have to
plan every second.

05:15.023 --> 05:18.526
Look. My dad dragged me
from one air force base
to another.

05:18.610 --> 05:20.444
Christmas was not
a priority for him.

05:20.570 --> 05:22.405
We...
We didn't even have a tree.

05:22.906 --> 05:24.991
Well, I want things
to be different
for my kids.

05:25.075 --> 05:28.661
I want them to have
big family traditions,
year after year,

05:28.745 --> 05:31.747
that they can
count on and...
And look forward to.

05:32.249 --> 05:33.708
You're right.

05:34.543 --> 05:36.377
I'm gonna try to
be more supportive.

05:36.503 --> 05:38.337
Well, you should be.

05:38.547 --> 05:41.590
Madison is a loner.
She has hardly any friends.

05:42.759 --> 05:46.262
Carter's a
10-year-old boy
with a midlife crisis.

05:47.097 --> 05:48.973
Let's face it.
Our kids are
a little weird.

05:49.766 --> 05:52.351
Well, I think
this year they need
Christmas more than ever.

05:52.936 --> 05:54.395
You're right.

05:54.980 --> 05:57.064
I'm sorry. You're right.

05:58.942 --> 06:03.404
Snowmen, eggnog,
caroling, we're gonna
do it all, okay?

06:03.488 --> 06:04.613
Okay.

06:14.291 --> 06:15.791
And I don't
write cookbooks.

06:16.918 --> 06:18.044
What?

06:18.128 --> 06:21.130
You always say that
I write cookbooks,
but I don't.

06:21.214 --> 06:23.132
I just edit
other people's recipes,

06:23.216 --> 06:26.052
and then I compile them
into cookbooks
that nobody buys.

06:26.136 --> 06:27.887
Then write your own.
Oh, great.

06:27.971 --> 06:30.890
So all the rejection
would just be more
personal? No, thank you.

06:30.974 --> 06:32.933
Well, I think you should.
Really?

06:33.018 --> 06:35.519
Yeah. I think you could.
Really?

06:35.604 --> 06:36.687
Sure.

06:37.814 --> 06:39.356
(TRUCK APPROACHING)

06:41.318 --> 06:42.902
What is that?

06:43.028 --> 06:44.570
Is it a truck?

06:44.654 --> 06:46.155
I don't know.

06:50.619 --> 06:51.619
(TRUCK ENGINE SPUTTERING)

06:56.500 --> 06:58.125
KELLY:
Ooh, it looks like
we have new neighbors.

06:58.210 --> 07:00.920
Who moves in
the middle of the night?
A meth lab?

07:04.132 --> 07:05.883
How bad could it be?

07:09.346 --> 07:10.346
Hmm.

07:16.103 --> 07:17.228
(MUTTERING)

07:17.312 --> 07:18.479
Okay.

07:39.668 --> 07:40.709
Oh! Oh! Ow!

07:40.794 --> 07:41.961
Whoa, big guy.

07:42.045 --> 07:43.587
Take it easy.
Hot, hot. Hot.

07:43.672 --> 07:45.923
You're spazzin' out
on me. You're havin'
a seizure.

07:46.007 --> 07:49.969
Oh. I got Tasered once.
It looked exactly like that.

07:50.053 --> 07:52.805
And I'm man enough
to say I wet myself.

07:52.889 --> 07:53.889
Who are you?

07:54.224 --> 07:57.184
I'm Buddy Hall.
We just moved in
across the street.

07:57.602 --> 07:59.812
You don't happen to
have a cat, do you?
No.

07:59.896 --> 08:02.022
Oh, good. Because I was
moving in last night,

08:02.107 --> 08:04.233
I accidentally dropped
a fridge on one.

08:04.317 --> 08:06.193
Thank God most
of it got away.

08:06.278 --> 08:08.028
Buddy!
Tia!

08:08.488 --> 08:09.697
Come on over and meet...
Hey.

08:09.781 --> 08:11.574
What's your name?
Finch. Steve Finch,

08:11.658 --> 08:12.950
but this isn't
really a very good time.

08:13.076 --> 08:14.410
Come and meet Steve.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.494
Good morning!
Hi.

08:15.579 --> 08:19.915
Oh, well, Steve,
you have a way
with the ladies.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.084
Thanks.
Oh, um, thank you.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.377
My wife, Kelly.
This is Buddy.

08:23.503 --> 08:24.670
Kelly. Very nice
to meet you.

08:24.754 --> 08:25.921
Nice to meet you.
Honey,

08:26.006 --> 08:28.090
I measured. The ceiling's
too low in the bedroom.

08:28.425 --> 08:29.675
We're gonna have to
get a shorter pole.

08:29.759 --> 08:31.010
(BUDDY GROANS)

08:31.094 --> 08:32.635
Morning.
Hi.

08:32.761 --> 08:35.014
Oh, what'd he do,
try to steal your paper?

08:35.097 --> 08:36.974
No. I was just
being neighborly.

08:37.058 --> 08:39.518
Oh, leave you alone
for five minutes...
(MURMURS)

08:39.602 --> 08:41.227
(GASPS)
Looks like
we got a visitor.

08:41.313 --> 08:42.354
Oh!

08:44.608 --> 08:47.276
Don't put
the little guy away
on my account.

08:49.654 --> 08:52.323
Tia, this is Kelly.
Kelly, this is Tia.

08:52.407 --> 08:53.532
Hi. So nice to meet you.
Hi.

08:53.658 --> 08:54.825
You too.

08:54.910 --> 08:56.577
You have kids, right?
We do.

08:56.661 --> 08:58.037
Why don't you
come on over,

08:58.121 --> 09:00.289
and we should talk
about maybe starting
a carpool or somethin'.

09:00.373 --> 09:01.457
That sounds great.

09:01.541 --> 09:02.541
Welcome.
TIA: Thank you.

09:02.626 --> 09:03.626
Bye.

09:03.793 --> 09:04.793
Hey.

09:05.879 --> 09:07.046
Here.
Watch out.
It's hot.

09:07.130 --> 09:08.631
Ah! Ah!
Hot, hot, hot.

09:10.383 --> 09:11.592
Mmm. It's good.

09:12.302 --> 09:14.220
MADDY: I can't believe
you're making me do this.

09:14.304 --> 09:15.638
KELLY: We're just gonna
stop and say hello.

09:15.805 --> 09:16.805
(DOORBELL RINGS)

09:16.932 --> 09:18.557
(GRUNTS)
Come on in. It's open.

09:19.684 --> 09:20.726
Hello?

09:20.810 --> 09:25.231
Oh. Good. Oh, honey,
could you come over here
and give me a little boost?

09:25.649 --> 09:27.358
Oh, sure.
Seriously, sweetie.

09:27.484 --> 09:29.235
I'm about to
break my neck here.

09:29.319 --> 09:31.695
Just yank it up there.
Yeah. Just...
Yeah. A little bit harder.

09:31.780 --> 09:33.405
Oh.
More. Up.

09:33.490 --> 09:34.490
(YELPS)

09:35.158 --> 09:36.659
There you go.

09:37.285 --> 09:39.161
Whoo! That's one way
to get acquainted, huh?

09:39.246 --> 09:40.871
Oh, uh, these are for you.

09:41.456 --> 09:42.790
Oh, thank you.

09:42.874 --> 09:44.667
Oh, I love blueberry.

09:45.335 --> 09:46.919
Right to the hip.

09:49.005 --> 09:50.172
And who do
we have here?

09:50.298 --> 09:51.507
This is Madison.

09:51.841 --> 09:53.050
Say hello, Madison.

09:53.176 --> 09:54.468
Hello, Madison.

09:55.303 --> 09:57.012
She's 15.
You know how they get.

09:57.097 --> 09:58.931
TIA: You're kidding me.
Fifteen?

09:59.015 --> 10:00.641
My girls are 15.

10:01.393 --> 10:04.270
Girls,
get your butts down here!
We've got company!

10:04.521 --> 10:05.562
Carter. Carter.

10:05.689 --> 10:06.689
(GASPS)

10:06.856 --> 10:07.856
You're staring.

10:08.149 --> 10:09.275
Oh. Oh.

10:09.985 --> 10:12.319
Sorry about that.
I used to do
a little modeling.

10:12.696 --> 10:15.197
Mostly for art classes
at the community college.

10:15.532 --> 10:16.991
That's how I met Buddy.

10:17.075 --> 10:19.243
Really. Was he an artist?

10:19.619 --> 10:21.453
Nah. They caught
him peeking in
through the windows.

10:21.621 --> 10:22.871
(CHUCKLES)

10:23.498 --> 10:24.873
That...
That's such a sweet story.

10:25.292 --> 10:28.168
You know,
I just got so tired
of dating boys.

10:28.253 --> 10:29.628
No offense.
Mmm.

10:29.921 --> 10:31.922
Then one day
I met Buddy, and

10:32.382 --> 10:33.841
he just swept me
right off my feet.

10:34.092 --> 10:35.092
Oh.

10:35.218 --> 10:36.343
TIA: Oh, there you are.

10:37.220 --> 10:40.848
These are my babies,
Ashley and Emily.

10:41.516 --> 10:43.183
KELLY: Hi, girls.
BOTH: Hi.

10:43.268 --> 10:45.269
This is Madison,
and this is Carter.

10:45.353 --> 10:46.353
Hi.

10:46.438 --> 10:49.732
You know,
you girls will probably be
in a lot of the same classes.

10:49.983 --> 10:52.234
Great.
Are there any hot guys?

10:52.360 --> 10:53.360
Uh...

10:53.570 --> 10:56.488
Yeah, but, you know,
they're all enormous tools.

10:56.573 --> 10:58.157
Really?
Will you introduce us?

10:58.241 --> 10:59.992
Oh!
Kelly, thank you.

11:00.076 --> 11:01.410
That has been in
my family for years.

11:01.536 --> 11:02.786
Oh, it's beautiful.

11:02.871 --> 11:03.829
It ought to be.

11:03.913 --> 11:05.622
It's worth more
than this entire house
put together.

11:05.832 --> 11:06.832
(CHUCKLES)

11:07.083 --> 11:08.167
Let me just find
a safe place for it,

11:08.251 --> 11:09.626
and we'll see about
getting these kids to school.

11:09.711 --> 11:12.504
I can drop them
at school if you want
to stay and unpack.

11:12.589 --> 11:13.630
Really?

11:13.715 --> 11:15.299
Sure.
You'd do that for me?

11:15.383 --> 11:16.842
Yeah. No problem.
I'll just...

11:16.926 --> 11:18.969
I'll bring the car around
while they get dressed.

11:19.054 --> 11:20.304
Oh, they are dressed.
Trust me.

11:20.388 --> 11:21.930
This is more clothes
than they've worn
in months.

11:23.058 --> 11:24.433
Can I live here?

11:24.559 --> 11:25.934
Get in the car.

11:27.771 --> 11:29.355
You got
a fake I. D?

11:29.481 --> 11:31.023
Uh. No. No.

11:31.107 --> 11:32.232
Don't worry.
We can make you one.

11:32.359 --> 11:33.484
Nice girls.

11:33.568 --> 11:35.361
You kidding me?
I pray every day
for the strength

11:35.445 --> 11:38.197
not to run over
the both of them
with a truck.

11:38.281 --> 11:39.281
Have a nice day!

11:39.616 --> 11:41.950
MAN: All right.
Listen up, you guys.
We just got in

11:42.202 --> 11:44.078
a new shipment
of Aspens.

11:44.496 --> 11:47.456
And I want you to
sell three for me
by lunchtime. All right.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.041
What, are you kidding?

11:49.125 --> 11:51.293
Hey. We got
a new salesman.
Buddy Hall over here.

11:51.378 --> 11:52.419
Let's make him
feel welcome.

11:52.504 --> 11:53.587
Come on. Yeah.
How you doin'?

11:53.671 --> 11:54.963
All right.
All right. All right.

11:55.090 --> 11:56.382
Hi.

11:57.550 --> 11:58.884
Welcome aboard.

11:58.968 --> 12:00.677
Sell, sell, sell.
All right.

12:02.764 --> 12:03.972
(SOFTLY) Okay.

12:04.391 --> 12:06.475
(WHISPERING) Oh, this
is gonna be good. Oh!

12:06.559 --> 12:07.559
Oh.
Buddy!

12:07.644 --> 12:08.644
Hey. You, uh...

12:08.728 --> 12:10.729
Gee, you ready
to sell some cars?

12:10.814 --> 12:13.107
Me? I'm a born
car salesman.

12:13.191 --> 12:14.733
But I was
thinking today that

12:14.818 --> 12:17.194
maybe I would just
kind of ease into it.

12:17.278 --> 12:18.946
You know,
get a feeling for the place.

12:19.030 --> 12:21.990
Yeah, well...
Well, you see that
tire-kicker right there?

12:22.575 --> 12:23.700
He's all yours.

12:23.868 --> 12:24.868
Hmm.

12:25.161 --> 12:26.328
I don't know. I...

12:26.413 --> 12:28.705
I got a thousand bucks
says you can't sell him.

12:28.790 --> 12:30.165
Let me in
on that action.

12:30.291 --> 12:31.792
You know...
Thousand bucks?

12:31.876 --> 12:33.085
...let's just
make it three.

12:33.169 --> 12:34.545
Three?
TED: Three g's.

12:37.424 --> 12:39.174
All right.
You guys are asking for it.

12:41.344 --> 12:43.637
There's one born
every minute. Come on.

12:45.181 --> 12:46.890
MAN: Ted, this is genius.

12:47.267 --> 12:49.852
You can't let
these new guys
get into a rhythm.

12:50.478 --> 12:52.396
I'm telling you, boys.
From this day forward,

12:53.857 --> 12:54.898
we own that guy.

12:55.358 --> 12:57.359
There we go.
The brush-off.

12:57.527 --> 12:59.361
That's the brush-off.
The brush-off. Okay.

13:05.535 --> 13:06.577
(ALL LAUGHING)

13:06.661 --> 13:07.661
We got ya!

13:07.745 --> 13:08.829
Are you okay?

13:08.872 --> 13:10.998
You walked face-first
into that buzz saw.
(IMITATES SAW)

13:11.916 --> 13:15.252
Money on my desk
by the end of the day.
No checks.

13:18.089 --> 13:19.423
That... That's
not possible.

13:19.507 --> 13:21.717
Mr. Murray
owns the dealership.

13:27.390 --> 13:29.475
I just bought
one of my own cars.

13:32.854 --> 13:36.064
And the worst part
is I paid sticker.

13:41.905 --> 13:42.946
Hey, girls.

13:43.031 --> 13:44.406
Hey, Dad.
Hi, Dad.

13:46.201 --> 13:47.659
(KNIFE CHOPPING)

13:52.081 --> 13:53.081
(SIGHS)

13:55.502 --> 13:56.585
And?

13:56.711 --> 13:57.711
(SIGHS)

13:58.087 --> 13:59.880
Sold a car
the first five minutes!

13:59.964 --> 14:02.508
Buddy, no!
Oh, my God!

14:02.592 --> 14:04.593
Told you things
were gonna work out.
Yeah, yes.

14:04.677 --> 14:06.386
Oh, baby.
I'm so proud of you.
It's great.

14:06.471 --> 14:08.347
Great, great,
great, great, great.

14:08.431 --> 14:11.308
Yeah. Mmm.
It's great. Mmm.

14:11.935 --> 14:13.101
Buddy.
(MURMURS)

14:13.186 --> 14:14.394
Buddy?

14:14.479 --> 14:15.854
Buddy.
Yeah.

14:15.939 --> 14:17.439
Bud.
I know.

14:17.524 --> 14:20.150
Don't you even...
You always do this.

14:20.235 --> 14:22.402
You start out great.
You lose interest.

14:22.487 --> 14:25.989
And the next thing you know,
I'm up to my neck
in cardboard boxes.

14:26.074 --> 14:28.867
No, it's great.
I'm a car salesman.

14:28.952 --> 14:30.577
Hey. That's a good job.

14:30.662 --> 14:32.287
It's a great job.
Great job.

14:32.413 --> 14:33.997
Car salesman.
Yes.

14:34.082 --> 14:36.625
Carpets. Uh, copiers.

14:37.293 --> 14:38.669
Futons.

14:39.045 --> 14:40.045
(MUTTERS)

14:41.130 --> 14:42.798
It's all the same.

14:43.258 --> 14:45.592
I don't know.
I was just hoping that,

14:45.677 --> 14:48.428
you know, one day
I'd do something big.

14:49.389 --> 14:51.139
Something important.

14:51.766 --> 14:53.559
Something monumental.

14:53.935 --> 14:56.436
You are.
You're going to pay off
our monumental debt.

14:57.313 --> 14:58.313
(GRUMBLES)

14:58.731 --> 15:00.315
Buddy, you promised me.

15:00.817 --> 15:04.069
Oh. Well, I will
keep my promise.

15:04.153 --> 15:05.320
That was a little...

15:05.446 --> 15:06.572
Everything's
gonna be great.

15:06.656 --> 15:08.699
Oh, yes.
(MURMURING)

15:10.159 --> 15:11.410
Daddy.
Daddy, come look.

15:11.661 --> 15:12.953
(TOGETHER)
We got something real cool.

15:13.037 --> 15:14.705
Oh, the honeys.

15:16.082 --> 15:17.332
TOGETHER: Hey, Dad.
Mmm.

15:17.834 --> 15:20.335
You're sweet. Mmm!

15:20.962 --> 15:22.254
What do you
got goin' here?

15:22.380 --> 15:23.714
It's My Earth.

15:23.798 --> 15:25.257
My Earth?
You type in an address,

15:25.341 --> 15:28.427
and you can see
every house in the
country from space.

15:28.511 --> 15:29.928
Really?
Mm-hmm.

15:30.013 --> 15:33.181
Emily's already used
it to track the, like,
five hottest guys in school.

15:33.266 --> 15:35.392
Yeah, Dad.
Three of them live
two blocks from here.

15:35.476 --> 15:38.145
Wow. That's more math
than you've done in years.

15:38.229 --> 15:39.896
Did it hurt?
Loser.

15:40.648 --> 15:42.858
Easy. You can see
every house from space?

15:42.942 --> 15:44.568
Yeah.
Let's see.

15:52.201 --> 15:53.660
Where's our house?

15:53.786 --> 15:55.287
Oh, you can't
see our house.

15:55.538 --> 15:56.830
EMILY: But you can
see the neighbors'.

15:57.457 --> 15:58.790
That figures.
We're invisible.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.751
Buddy, trash.

16:00.960 --> 16:01.960
Mmm.

16:03.129 --> 16:04.129
Hmm.

16:05.048 --> 16:06.381
Space, huh?

16:16.726 --> 16:19.227
Of course you can see
the big house.

16:44.087 --> 16:46.213
See it from space.

16:48.758 --> 16:50.425
I'll light it up.

16:54.681 --> 16:55.681
(CHUCKLES)

16:55.765 --> 16:58.100
Not gonna be
invisible anymore.

16:58.643 --> 17:00.811
(LOUD BANGING)

17:07.359 --> 17:08.984
3:00 in the morning.
(BANGS)

17:09.112 --> 17:10.569
Unbelievable.
(BANGS)

17:13.616 --> 17:15.117
(HAMMERING)

17:20.123 --> 17:21.289
Oh, man.

17:23.459 --> 17:24.626
Buddy.

17:25.670 --> 17:27.462
Buddy.
Hey, Steve.

17:28.214 --> 17:30.132
Do you have any idea
what time it is?

17:30.216 --> 17:32.509
What's the matter?
All the clocks in
your house busted?

17:32.593 --> 17:34.678
No, I know
what time it is.

17:35.096 --> 17:36.596
Oh. What, did ya

17:36.681 --> 17:39.099
just need an excuse
to come over here
in your underwear?

17:39.183 --> 17:41.059
No. No.
I was being sarcastic.

17:41.811 --> 17:43.979
Oh. Well,
you gotta know that stuff

17:44.147 --> 17:46.314
like that just goes
right over my head.

17:46.399 --> 17:47.441
Here. Hold these things.

17:47.525 --> 17:48.567
I want to strand them out.

17:48.693 --> 17:49.735
No. I will not
hold on to this.

17:49.819 --> 17:53.280
That's why I came over
here. You're making
all kinds of noise.

17:53.364 --> 17:55.866
Do you have any idea
how bright your house is?

17:55.950 --> 17:58.160
Yeah. It's pretty
damn bright.

17:59.162 --> 18:00.954
BUDDY: Look at that. Whoo!

18:02.206 --> 18:05.459
Oh. Is that what's
bothering you? The lights?

18:05.793 --> 18:07.627
Yes. That's right.
Oh, I'm sorry.

18:07.754 --> 18:09.963
I didn't mean it.
I'll turn them off.
Thank you.

18:10.047 --> 18:11.673
Oh.
Thank you.

18:11.758 --> 18:12.799
Steve.

18:14.802 --> 18:16.178
Are we gonna be friends?

18:16.262 --> 18:19.473
Because,
you know, we just moved
into the neighborhood, and

18:20.016 --> 18:23.560
boy, it would be bad
if I ticked off
the only guy I know.

18:24.437 --> 18:26.188
That would kill me.

18:26.272 --> 18:29.107
Well, maybe I overreacted
a little bit.

18:30.151 --> 18:32.736
Ah, you know, I can be
a real jerk sometimes.

18:32.820 --> 18:35.822
Maybe we should just
start completely over.

18:38.701 --> 18:39.868
Buddy Hall. And you are?

18:40.703 --> 18:42.120
No. I didn't mean
we should literally.

18:42.205 --> 18:45.081
I was...
I was speaking metaphorically.

18:46.209 --> 18:47.209
Pew!

18:48.044 --> 18:49.294
That's it. I don't...

18:49.378 --> 18:52.506
Sometimes
my stupidity astounds me.

18:54.842 --> 18:57.719
I got an idea.
How about if you and I

18:57.804 --> 18:59.846
come up with
a series of hand signals,

18:59.931 --> 19:02.098
so I'll know when
you're gonna talk weird?

19:04.852 --> 19:05.894
I'll see you tomorrow.

19:10.024 --> 19:11.775
This is gonna be good.
Come on.
It's so late.

19:11.859 --> 19:14.444
Get that satellite
image up that you
had before.

19:14.529 --> 19:16.613
Go on. Here.
Honey, you sit here.
Really?

19:16.697 --> 19:18.782
Yeah. Sit right
there and watch. Yeah.

19:18.866 --> 19:20.867
There's so many buttons.
I'll do it. Move.

19:20.952 --> 19:23.787
Do it. Do it.
Okay. You do it.
Where you going?

19:23.871 --> 19:25.872
Stick around.
I want you to see this.

19:26.249 --> 19:27.207
You still can't see it.

19:27.291 --> 19:28.291
You're gonna miss it.

19:28.376 --> 19:30.043
Sorry, Daddy.
What do you mean
you can't see it?

19:30.127 --> 19:32.921
It's impossible.
I put so many
more lights on.

19:33.005 --> 19:35.298
Oh, honey,
you're gonna get it.
You'll get it.

19:35.383 --> 19:36.466
(GROANS)

19:41.556 --> 19:42.597
I gotta go bigger.

19:51.941 --> 19:53.149
Oh, hi.

19:53.234 --> 19:54.401
Can you order me
more of these?

19:54.527 --> 19:55.694
Sure.

19:55.778 --> 19:56.778
Yeah?
Yeah.

19:57.446 --> 19:58.822
What's that?

19:59.448 --> 20:02.158
(CHUCKLES)
You're gonna love this.

20:05.746 --> 20:08.999
It's a horse-drawn sleigh.

20:09.083 --> 20:10.876
Don't see many of
these around anymore.

20:10.960 --> 20:12.043
No, you don't.

20:12.169 --> 20:13.253
Nice.

20:15.798 --> 20:16.798
I'll take it!

20:17.925 --> 20:19.301
No.
Come on.

20:19.385 --> 20:20.427
No.
Why?

20:20.511 --> 20:22.220
Get away from me with that.
What do you mean?

20:22.305 --> 20:23.972
I'm serious.
I'll call Child Services.

20:24.098 --> 20:25.765
One look at that,
and they will put you away.

20:26.434 --> 20:27.976
Maddy. Maddy. We...

20:28.060 --> 20:31.021
We always wear
matching sweaters
for the family Christmas card.

20:31.105 --> 20:34.774
Come on.
It's all right. Huh? Please?

20:35.318 --> 20:37.152
Hmm? Look, huh?

20:39.822 --> 20:40.989
Please.

20:41.657 --> 20:43.033
Are we ready?

20:43.159 --> 20:44.576
There. You see?
Mom's wearing hers.

20:45.036 --> 20:47.120
Okay.
Mom's old and married.

20:47.204 --> 20:48.622
All right? She doesn't
need the self-esteem.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.165
I still have
something to live for.

20:50.499 --> 20:52.667
It's true.
Madison's right.

20:53.377 --> 20:55.170
She's got her whole life
ahead of her.

20:55.796 --> 20:58.006
That's more than I can say
for some of us.

20:58.382 --> 21:00.300
Come on.
He does this every year.

21:00.384 --> 21:02.427
He starts acting
all depressed so people
feel bad for him

21:02.511 --> 21:03.845
and buy him
bigger presents.

21:04.347 --> 21:06.097
Hey. The new
neighbors have reindeer.

21:06.724 --> 21:08.058
TOGETHER: Reindeer?

21:08.184 --> 21:09.559
Wait. Wait. Wait.

21:11.354 --> 21:13.605
BUDDY: Hey, Steve.
What do you think?

21:13.856 --> 21:15.690
Oh, my God.
(CHUCKLES)

21:15.775 --> 21:18.902
It's so cute.
Where in the world
did you find it?

21:18.986 --> 21:21.780
Eugene Young down
at the hardware store
sold it to him.

21:21.864 --> 21:22.906
Isn't it beautiful?

21:23.032 --> 21:24.115
Beautiful.

21:24.200 --> 21:26.242
Yes. And...
And these horses.

21:26.327 --> 21:29.204
These horses... I...
I especially like the way

21:29.288 --> 21:31.289
you've duct-taped
the antlers to their heads.

21:31.374 --> 21:35.460
Yeah, well,
apparently, reindeer are not
indigenous to the region.

21:35.544 --> 21:37.295
ASHLEY:
That sweater is really cool.

21:37.380 --> 21:38.630
Yeah.
Is it Marc Jacobs?

21:38.756 --> 21:40.006
Oh.

21:40.466 --> 21:41.925
You know, I'm not sure.
I have so many,

21:42.009 --> 21:43.885
it's kind of hard to
keep track these days.

21:44.387 --> 21:45.887
(HORSE WHINNIES)

21:46.222 --> 21:47.681
Well, this has been fun.

21:47.765 --> 21:49.808
So, let's go...
Let's go take
the picture, huh?

21:50.226 --> 21:51.267
Wait. What picture?

21:51.352 --> 21:52.894
Are you talking about
your Christmas picture?
Mm-hmm.

21:53.020 --> 21:54.646
You should take it
here in the sled.

21:54.730 --> 21:55.981
That's a great idea!
Oh, yeah.

21:56.065 --> 21:59.150
No, that's
a horrible idea
because

21:59.235 --> 22:01.111
we always take
our picture in front
of the fireplace.

22:01.195 --> 22:02.445
It's a tradition.

22:02.530 --> 22:04.823
But wouldn't it
be nice to try
something new this year?

22:04.907 --> 22:06.741
I don't think so. No.
Here's a hat.

22:06.826 --> 22:08.493
No.
Take the picture
in the sled.

22:08.577 --> 22:09.661
Oh, no, no.

22:09.787 --> 22:10.912
Put the Santa suit on.
Yes, no.

22:11.288 --> 22:12.288
You're gonna take
the picture in the sled.

22:12.415 --> 22:13.415
That's silly.

22:13.499 --> 22:14.499
That's the way
to do it.

22:14.625 --> 22:15.625
It's adorable.

22:15.710 --> 22:17.335
Carter, get out
of that right now.

22:17.420 --> 22:20.171
Also, we should
keep our voices down
a little bit because

22:20.256 --> 22:22.882
I found these horses on
the outskirts of town,

22:22.967 --> 22:25.593
and between you and me,
they look a little skittish.

22:26.262 --> 22:28.013
You found these horses?
Yeah.

22:28.097 --> 22:29.180
Carter...

22:29.306 --> 22:30.432
No, no.
...out of that
death trap now!

22:31.017 --> 22:32.892
Come on.
All right, Carter.
Let's go.

22:32.977 --> 22:34.811
Give me the reins.
Give me the reins.
Come on, Carter.

22:34.895 --> 22:36.604
Let go of the reins.

22:36.897 --> 22:37.897
(WHINNIES)

22:43.112 --> 22:44.904
Whoa! Whoa!

22:45.156 --> 22:46.239
Oh, my God!
Let's go.

22:46.323 --> 22:47.782
Honey!
Steve!

22:48.034 --> 22:49.284
(ALL SHOUTING)

22:49.493 --> 22:50.702
Honey!

22:50.786 --> 22:51.953
(WHINNYING)

22:52.038 --> 22:53.455
Run, run, run, run!
Honey!

22:53.748 --> 22:56.166
Whoa! Stop, horses!
Whoa! Whoa!

22:56.459 --> 22:58.043
Oh, sh... Whoa!

22:59.628 --> 23:00.795
Whoa!

23:02.631 --> 23:03.757
That's not good.

23:04.341 --> 23:05.341
(CAR ALARM BLARES)

23:05.509 --> 23:06.801
Whoa! Whoa!

23:09.472 --> 23:10.889
How do you steer this thing?

23:12.391 --> 23:13.475
Whoa!
(HORN HONKS)

23:17.480 --> 23:19.522
Out of the way!
Out of the way!

23:19.982 --> 23:21.066
Whoa!

23:21.442 --> 23:22.525
Oh, Mrs. Ryor!

23:23.027 --> 23:24.069
Whoa.

23:24.153 --> 23:25.653
Oh, oh. Fifi!
(WHIMPERS)

23:28.491 --> 23:29.574
Whoa. Whoa.

23:31.577 --> 23:32.786
(BOTH WHIMPERING)

23:32.995 --> 23:34.370
Whoa! Whoa!

23:38.667 --> 23:39.667
Ah.

23:41.045 --> 23:42.295
Oh, my!

23:43.923 --> 23:45.465
Whoo. Whoo.

23:45.549 --> 23:46.549
(SCREAMS)

23:47.343 --> 23:49.677
Santa! He's real!

23:50.137 --> 23:52.889
I knew it! I knew it!

23:57.353 --> 23:58.311
Ow!

23:58.395 --> 23:59.395
(GROANING)

24:01.190 --> 24:02.190
Ah!

24:03.651 --> 24:04.651
Ooh!

24:07.571 --> 24:08.863
(SCREAMING)

24:08.948 --> 24:09.948
Oh!

24:10.574 --> 24:11.825
Oh, boy!

24:13.452 --> 24:15.036
(GROANING)

24:24.505 --> 24:26.339
(BIRD WARBLES)

24:32.304 --> 24:34.055
BUDDY:
Oh. He's coming to.

24:34.140 --> 24:36.432
I think he's
gonna be all right.

24:37.476 --> 24:38.893
Where am I?

24:38.978 --> 24:43.314
We're in the backseat
of your wife's car
on the way to the hospital.

24:43.399 --> 24:44.399
You warming up?

24:44.567 --> 24:45.567
Yeah.

24:48.154 --> 24:50.029
Where are my clothes?

24:50.114 --> 24:53.741
You were freezing
to death. We had to
get you out of them.

24:56.245 --> 24:58.121
Where are
your clothes?

24:58.205 --> 25:01.666
I had to get your
body temperature up,
so I stripped us both down

25:01.750 --> 25:04.252
and zipped us into
this sleeping bag.

25:05.379 --> 25:08.423
Trust me. It works.
I've done it
a half a dozen times.

25:10.926 --> 25:12.635
(SCREAMING)

25:15.014 --> 25:16.306
Calm down. Calm down.

25:16.557 --> 25:18.266
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

25:20.811 --> 25:22.520
The doctor said
he probably saved
your life.

25:22.938 --> 25:25.148
Which is only fair,
since he's the one

25:25.274 --> 25:27.525
who almost got me
killed in the first place.
(HORNS HONKING)

25:27.610 --> 25:30.028
Oh, this used to be such
a nice, quiet neighborhood.

25:30.112 --> 25:33.156
Look at it now.
People driving
by all night.

25:33.449 --> 25:34.657
(HORNS HONKING)

25:34.742 --> 25:36.075
(CHATTERING)

25:38.495 --> 25:39.746
You see that?

25:39.830 --> 25:42.373
You see that?
I think he's
tapping into our power.

25:42.708 --> 25:46.044
Yes. And in the process,
he is stealing
our very souls.

25:46.128 --> 25:48.379
Well, how do you
think he's powering
all those lights of his?

25:48.464 --> 25:50.340
Honey,
I really think you're
wrong about him.

25:50.466 --> 25:52.383
Look at what
he dropped off.

25:52.468 --> 25:53.718
He knew we didn't
get a chance to take

25:53.844 --> 25:55.136
a picture for
our Christmas card,

25:55.221 --> 25:57.805
so look what he made
from a picture he
took at the hospital.

25:58.974 --> 26:00.391
That's you,
with the blue lips.

26:00.476 --> 26:01.476
Yeah.

26:01.560 --> 26:04.771
Yeah.
And a cute little oxygen tube
coming from your nose.

26:04.855 --> 26:07.023
Yeah. I picked up
on that. Thanks.

26:07.399 --> 26:10.777
Come on now.
That is a nice gesture,
don't you think?

26:10.861 --> 26:11.986
Okay.

26:12.905 --> 26:16.282
Okay. Yeah, maybe.
I don't know.
Maybe. I don't know.

26:16.659 --> 26:19.535
I think that we should
take them with us
to get the tree.

26:19.620 --> 26:21.371
No!
Yes.

26:21.455 --> 26:23.498
'Cause I really
like Tia.
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

26:23.582 --> 26:25.333
She's taken
a real interest
in my cookbooks.

26:25.584 --> 26:28.920
And you just need
to find a way to get
along with Buddy.

26:29.004 --> 26:31.047
Okay. But he's not
touching any of my trees.

26:31.382 --> 26:33.341
Okay, fine.
But they're
coming with us.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.385
Hey, Mom.
Hi, sweetie.

26:36.011 --> 26:38.680
Hey, Dad.
I was thinking.

26:39.348 --> 26:41.307
Maybe you could
take me Christmas
shopping for Mom.

26:41.767 --> 26:44.143
We could go to the mall
and wander around...

26:44.228 --> 26:45.228
Oh! And we can
get hot chocolate!

26:45.354 --> 26:46.396
You know what?

26:46.480 --> 26:47.897
Already taken care of.

26:47.982 --> 26:50.650
You're getting her
a really nice sweater that
I ordered from a catalog.

26:50.859 --> 26:51.859
Oh.

26:52.403 --> 26:54.279
I guess that
means we don't have
to go to the mall together.

26:54.363 --> 26:55.571
Yeah. Isn't that great?

26:55.990 --> 26:58.032
That place is
an insane asylum
this time of year.

26:59.159 --> 27:00.743
(CROWD CHATTERING)

27:00.828 --> 27:02.036
(CHUCKLES)

27:04.290 --> 27:05.415
(HORN HONKS)

27:05.499 --> 27:07.208
A little more power.

27:10.671 --> 27:11.713
Did you see that?

27:12.214 --> 27:13.881
Yeah.
You did?

27:16.385 --> 27:17.635
(CACKLING)

27:21.015 --> 27:22.390
(CROWD CHATTERING)

27:23.392 --> 27:24.851
(HORN HONKING)

27:31.150 --> 27:32.150
(DOOR CLOSES)

27:42.995 --> 27:45.288
Come on, kids.
Carter, come on.

27:47.207 --> 27:49.876
Oh. You guys have
your own lot. "Private."

27:49.960 --> 27:52.712
Yes. Isn't it great?
Steve's been
working on it for years.

27:52.796 --> 27:54.505
So nice.
We love it.

27:54.590 --> 27:56.883
Oh, this is amazing,
honey. Look.

27:58.385 --> 27:59.761
Wow.
Whoa.

28:00.054 --> 28:02.472
It's a nice
tree, honey.
BUDDY: What have you got here?

28:02.556 --> 28:04.265
Nice? It's perfect.

28:05.059 --> 28:06.601
A 12-foot Silver Noble.

28:06.935 --> 28:09.771
Yes, sir.
This is the way God
intended trees to look.

28:10.105 --> 28:12.899
What do you do?
Chop 'em down
or launch 'em?

28:12.983 --> 28:14.108
(GIRLS GIGGLE)

28:14.193 --> 28:15.318
Laugh all you want,

28:15.402 --> 28:17.820
but I got the next five years
of trees all lined up.

28:18.447 --> 28:19.781
And each one of
them is perfect.

28:20.115 --> 28:22.617
No twisted trunks,
no bald spots.

28:23.243 --> 28:26.287
Well, it's certainly
a dandy tree.
I'll give you that.

28:26.372 --> 28:28.373
Honeys, let's go.

28:28.457 --> 28:29.582
Yeah, Dad.
Let's find a really big one.

28:29.708 --> 28:30.792
Yeah.

28:30.876 --> 28:32.085
But it has to be pretty.

28:32.211 --> 28:33.419
Hey.

28:34.296 --> 28:37.256
The last ones
to the car are losers.

28:40.219 --> 28:42.387
Please.
It's not like it's a race.

28:42.471 --> 28:44.263
Give me the ax, Carter.
No way he beats us.

28:44.348 --> 28:46.432
Honey, you said
he could cut it down.

28:46.517 --> 28:48.935
Well, he can do it next year.
Come on. Give me the ax.

28:50.479 --> 28:52.105
It's all right,
sweetheart.
Come on.

28:52.564 --> 28:53.606
STEVE: What's the record?

28:53.732 --> 28:54.732
MADDY: Wow, Dad.

28:54.817 --> 28:57.735
I think I wrote it
down in my diary,
but I must have forgot.

28:57.861 --> 29:00.988
Ha-ha. Very funny.
But we'll be halfway
home by the time he...

29:01.323 --> 29:02.740
(CHAIN SAW WHIRRING)

29:09.498 --> 29:10.832
Does anyone smell gas?

29:12.042 --> 29:14.377
Well, it's probably me,
but cut me some slack.

29:14.461 --> 29:16.421
I'm swinging
pretty hard.

29:19.258 --> 29:20.258
(ALL GASP)

29:21.510 --> 29:23.052
Oh, my God!
Mom.

29:25.848 --> 29:27.598
KELLY:
Sweetheart, do something.

29:27.724 --> 29:29.475
What?
What happened?

