prestigious position.
Mmm!

32:55.557 --> 32:56.557
You have races?
What kind of races?

32:56.725 --> 32:57.725
Speed skating.

32:57.809 --> 32:59.769
Speed skating?
We do it right here.

32:59.853 --> 33:01.937
They put the ice
right on Main Street.

33:02.856 --> 33:04.231
I used to do a little
speed skating myself.

33:04.358 --> 33:05.691
Really? (CHUCKLES)

33:05.776 --> 33:06.776
Well, so did I.

33:06.902 --> 33:07.943
MAN: Excuse me.

33:09.154 --> 33:10.738
Wallace Fiskin.
Oh!

33:11.281 --> 33:12.573
Buddy Hall.
Sir,

33:12.658 --> 33:14.659
meeting you is
one of the great
moments of my life.

33:15.452 --> 33:17.745
Well, thank you, Wallace.
It's a pleasure to meet you.

33:18.372 --> 33:19.413
So, anyway,

33:20.457 --> 33:22.708
how do you feel
about the liberal
use of mistletoe?

33:23.251 --> 33:28.005
Well, I feel that
you should go sparingly
around the threshold,

33:28.090 --> 33:29.674
because that's a clichÃ©.

33:30.092 --> 33:31.967
Please. Please.

33:32.636 --> 33:33.678
My mission is clear.

33:33.762 --> 33:35.554
Wallace, thank you.
Good luck.

33:35.681 --> 33:37.640
Would you take
this inside for me?
Oh, my pleasure.

33:37.724 --> 33:39.475
Steve! Oh, Steve!

33:41.228 --> 33:42.770
I guess
I'm the new Christmas guy.

33:44.773 --> 33:48.025
That's okay.
You can take Toe Jam Day.

33:48.610 --> 33:49.610
Oh.

33:50.028 --> 33:51.487
This isn't over yet.

33:51.571 --> 33:54.865
We're just getting started.
I'm the Christmas guy.

33:54.950 --> 33:56.450
I'm the Christmas guy!

33:58.286 --> 33:59.787
(STEVE VOCALIZING)

34:00.038 --> 34:03.624
Honey,
Tia just gave me
a great idea.

34:04.418 --> 34:06.127
I'm gonna write
my own cookbook.

34:06.670 --> 34:07.753
That's my girl.

34:07.879 --> 34:08.920
Tia gave you the idea?

34:09.005 --> 34:10.297
I've been telling you
to do that for years.

34:10.465 --> 34:11.757
You know what?

34:11.842 --> 34:16.846
It should be a cookbook
for real moms who
cook for real families!

34:16.929 --> 34:18.389
Yes!

34:18.473 --> 34:20.266
(GASPS)
And I have the title for you.

34:20.350 --> 34:22.518
Food-Food with Kelly Finch.

34:22.811 --> 34:24.437
I love it!

34:24.521 --> 34:26.313
MADDY: Dad, there's
about 50 singing dorks

34:26.481 --> 34:28.315
waiting for you
in the front yard!

34:29.192 --> 34:30.818
Fifty. Isn't that great?
(CROWD CHATTERING FAINTLY)

34:30.902 --> 34:32.402
You know what?

34:32.946 --> 34:35.697
You are gonna help me
write the cookbook.

34:35.824 --> 34:36.824
(GASPING)

34:36.992 --> 34:38.033
Okay!

34:38.118 --> 34:39.994
Yes? Yea!
I'd be happy to!

34:40.370 --> 34:42.871
KELLY: Kids!
(STEVE VOCALIZING)

34:43.206 --> 34:45.373
Wow! Nice!

34:45.751 --> 34:47.042
Where are your clothes?

34:47.168 --> 34:48.502
Calm down.
I have a jacket.

34:48.837 --> 34:50.588
Well, keep it zipped.

34:51.465 --> 34:52.465
So, where are the twins?

34:52.549 --> 34:54.425
They'll be over
just as soon as
the boys get here.

34:54.760 --> 34:57.344
Boys? Boys? Madison
is not allowed to date.

34:57.429 --> 35:01.140
Honey, don't worry.
It's a one-time thing.
They ship out next week.

35:01.224 --> 35:02.349
They're in the navy?

35:02.517 --> 35:03.642
Bye, Dad!

35:04.352 --> 35:07.480
Wait! Wait!
Wait! Wait!

35:08.690 --> 35:09.940
(ALL CHEERING)

35:10.692 --> 35:14.111
Oh. Thank you for coming,
and thank you for...

35:14.529 --> 35:15.988
For braving the insanity.

35:17.032 --> 35:19.950
I have the songbooks here,
so let's pass them
amongst yourselves.

35:20.035 --> 35:21.869
(GERTA SPEAKING GERMAN)

35:23.371 --> 35:25.748
Oh, yes, do you have
"There's An Acorn
In My Stocking"?

35:26.041 --> 35:27.082
Uh, no, I...

35:27.167 --> 35:28.751
(GERMAN)

35:29.920 --> 35:31.796
Yes, do you have
"The Ignorant Snowman"?

35:31.880 --> 35:33.214
No, I don't think I do.
But we can...

35:33.298 --> 35:35.549
Hey, there's a news crew
over at the Halls.

35:35.801 --> 35:38.969
Yeah, it really is
quite a spectacle.

35:39.054 --> 35:40.679
Anyway, I thought that
we would start with

35:40.806 --> 35:42.473
one of my...
My very favorites,

35:42.557 --> 35:44.600
"The Holly and the lvy."

35:44.684 --> 35:45.893
Pitch pipe.

35:46.019 --> 35:47.186
Oh. Sorry.

35:47.270 --> 35:50.356
Ah! Hi! (GIGGLES)
Have a good time!
Sing away!

35:50.440 --> 35:52.316
Sorry, honey.
Go ahead.

35:53.235 --> 35:54.276
Thanks for coming!

35:55.070 --> 35:56.362
(SINGING CHRISTMAS CAROL)

35:56.446 --> 35:57.446
(HIP-HOP ON LOUDSPEAKERS)

36:01.159 --> 36:02.576
I love that song!

36:02.744 --> 36:04.161
No, wait! Wait! Come back!

36:04.913 --> 36:07.665
Come back here!
We're not done with rehearsal!

36:07.749 --> 36:09.583
Come back. We're not...
We're going caroling.

36:09.668 --> 36:11.585
It's a... It's a tradition.
Everybody...

36:12.295 --> 36:13.754
Honey! You!

36:15.131 --> 36:16.257
I'm not going anywhere.

36:18.301 --> 36:20.052
Where are the kids?
Um...

36:22.180 --> 36:25.391
Oh, look. They are
going to be making
kissing and so.

36:25.475 --> 36:27.601
Ja. Kissing
and so. Ja.

36:27.686 --> 36:29.645
Hello there.
We're from Channel 8 News,

36:29.771 --> 36:31.730
and we would love
to have an interview.

36:31.815 --> 36:32.857
Where are they going?

36:32.941 --> 36:37.027
Hi. I... I'm just very
happy that everyone
likes the lights.

36:37.112 --> 36:38.195
Oh! (GIGGLES)

36:38.989 --> 36:40.030
REPORTER: Yes, indeed.

36:40.115 --> 36:43.200
Obviously you have
put an awful lot
of work into this.

36:43.285 --> 36:46.036
Oh, yeah.
And I'm nowhere
near being finished.

36:46.121 --> 36:48.205
Oh, are you
kidding me? Jesus!

36:48.290 --> 36:49.290
(ALL GASPING)

36:50.625 --> 36:54.128
(SINGING)
...Christ, the Lord, is born
this Christmas morning

36:54.796 --> 36:55.838
Look at that.

36:55.922 --> 36:57.548
The lights have
obviously brought out

36:57.674 --> 36:59.300
the Christmas
spirit in everyone.

36:59.634 --> 37:03.721
Yeah. Yeah, they
bring out the Christmas
spirit in everybody.

37:03.805 --> 37:05.180
Yeah, I'm really
happy about that.

37:05.640 --> 37:06.682
Oh, my gosh.

37:06.766 --> 37:08.559
And I'm not gonna stop

37:08.643 --> 37:13.397
until I have the biggest
and brightest light display

37:13.481 --> 37:14.899
in the world.

37:14.983 --> 37:16.191
Oh, please.

37:16.318 --> 37:17.610
I also...

37:18.778 --> 37:22.156
I really want my
house to be seen

37:23.992 --> 37:24.992
from space!

37:25.744 --> 37:26.744
(ALL CHEERING)

37:27.120 --> 37:28.162
Oh, my God!

37:29.331 --> 37:30.372
Outer space.

37:30.624 --> 37:31.790
Oh, God!

37:31.917 --> 37:33.083
Honey. Wait!

37:33.168 --> 37:34.251
Wait. What are
you gonna do?

37:34.377 --> 37:35.419
You heard him,
didn't you?

37:35.503 --> 37:37.838
This is gonna
stop tonight!

37:38.006 --> 37:40.174
We'll see what Sheriff Dave
has to say about this.

37:40.508 --> 37:43.719
Does anybody know
who these R.V. S
belong to? Anybody?

37:44.054 --> 37:45.429
